大卫·鲍伊 (David Bowie) 在公共场合如何伪装自己https://www.nme.com/news/music/heres-how-david-bowie-used-to-disguise-himself-in-public-3763907?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=heres-how-david-bowie-习惯在公共场合伪装自己Max PilleySun, 09 Jun 2024 10:39:00 +0000 Music NewsNewsRockhttps://www.nme.com/?p=3763907 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="大卫·鲍伊" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>音乐公关传奇人物艾伦·爱德华兹 (Alan Edwards) 向 NME 解释了鲍伊在 80 年代如何使用一种简单的技巧来避免在公共场合受到关注</p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/heres-how-david-bowie-used-to-disguise-himself-in-public-3763907">《大卫·鲍伊 (David Bowie) 在公共场合如何伪装自己》</a>一文首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="大卫·鲍伊" decoding="async" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/david_bowie_1980s-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>音乐公关传奇人物艾伦·爱德华兹 (Alan Edwards) 向<i>NME</i>讲述了<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/david-bowie">大卫·鲍伊 (David Bowie)</a>在商业成功的鼎盛时期如何在公共场合伪装自己。 </p><ul><li data-leveltext="" data-font="Symbol" data-listid="229" data-list-defn-props="{&quot;335552541&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559684&quot;:-2,&quot;335559685&quot;:720,&quot;335559991&quot;:360,&quot;469769226&quot;:&quot;Symbol&quot;,&quot;469769242&quot;:[8226],&quot;469777803&quot;:&quot;left&quot;,&quot;469777804&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;469777815&quot;:&quot;hybridMultilevel&quot;}" aria-setsize="-1" data-aria-posinset="1" data-aria-level="1"><b>阅读更多：</b> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/pr-giant-alan-edwards-on-working-with-david-bowie-rolling-stones-amy-winehouse-3761381"><b>公关巨头艾伦·爱德华兹 (Alan Edwards) 谈及大卫·鲍伊 (David Bowie) 的合作时表示：“他是一位非凡的天才，同时也是一位纯洁、令人放松的绅士。”</b></a></li></ul><p>爱德华兹是著名公关电影《外部组织》的创始人，他与鲍伊以及<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-rolling-stones">滚石乐队</a>、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/prince">普林斯</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/britney-spears">布兰妮·斯皮尔斯等人一起工作。</a></p><p>他现在出版了他的回忆录《<i>我在那儿：摇滚生活的快讯</i>》，并<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/pr-giant-alan-edwards-on-working-with-david-bowie-rolling-stones-amy-winehouse-3761381">在</a>与<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/pr-giant-alan-edwards-on-working-with-david-bowie-rolling-stones-amy-winehouse-3761381"><i>NME</i></a> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/pr-giant-alan-edwards-on-working-with-david-bowie-rolling-stones-amy-winehouse-3761381">的对话中</a>透露了鲍伊在 80 年代初如何处理自己的名气。</p><p> “我在他拍完[大岛渚 1983 年与<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/ryuichi-sakamoto">坂本龙一</a>合作的战争史诗片] <i>《圣诞快乐，劳伦斯先生</i>》之后见到了他，所以他被当作电影明星一样对待——但他也因为‘低级’而被自己的厂牌抛弃了。而且《英雄》在商业上并没有像<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/bay-city-rollers">《Bay City Rollers》</a>这样的作品被认为那么好！”爱德华兹解释道。 </p><figure id="attachment_3762223" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3762223" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3762223" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Edwards-Bowie-Iman@2000x1270.jpg" alt="艾伦·爱德华兹与大卫·鲍伊和伊曼" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Edwards-Bowie-Iman@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Edwards-Bowie-Iman@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Edwards-Bowie-Iman@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Edwards-Bowie-Iman@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Edwards-Bowie-Iman@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Edwards-Bowie-Iman@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3762223" class="wp-caption-text">艾伦·爱德华兹与大卫·鲍伊和伊曼。图片来源：新闻界</figcaption></figure><p>“当我和他一起巡演时，我开始意识到他是多么的脚踏实地和迷人。他会出现在我们位于托特纳姆法院路的办公室，为每个人煮咖啡。”</p><p> “他告诉我，他不被认出的秘诀就是戴一顶布帽，腋下夹着一份希腊报纸。这样，如果有人质疑是否是他，他们会仔细观察并思考，‘嗯，这不可能……他显然是希腊人’。” </p><ul><li data-leveltext="" data-font="Symbol" data-listid="230" data-list-defn-props="{&quot;335552541&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559684&quot;:-2,&quot;335559685&quot;:720,&quot;335559991&quot;:360,&quot;469769226&quot;:&quot;Symbol&quot;,&quot;469769242&quot;:[8226],&quot;469777803&quot;:&quot;left&quot;,&quot;469777804&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;469777815&quot;:&quot;hybridMultilevel&quot;}" aria-setsize="-1" data-aria-posinset="2" data-aria-level="1"><b>阅读更多：</b><b> </b><a href="https://www.nme.com/features/david-bowie-a-portrait-of-the-artist-as-a-young-man-as-told-by-those-who-knew-him-best-2443649"><b>大卫·鲍伊 (David Bowie) 的早年经历——最了解他的人讲述的</b></a></li></ul><p>“采访也是如此，”他继续说道。 “我们很多时候都会坐火车，没有头等舱之类的，你会惊讶地发现有多少人会再三考虑，然后想：‘不可能是他，他只是一个坐着的人我们一起去曼彻斯特。</p><p> “书中的一个例子是，有一次在接受电台采访后，他无事可做，所以他决定展示电台的交通报告。他坐在那里告诉人们 M25 延误了……即使到了今天，我认为没有人知道那是大卫·鲍伊 (David Bowie)。他是一位非凡的创意天才，同时也是一位纯洁、令人放松、友善的绅士。”</p><p>在鲍伊的其他新闻中，帕西·肯西特 (Patsy Kensit) 最近回顾了<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/patsy-kensit-remembers-strange-hair-brushing-encounter-with-david-bowie-3618140">她曾经与这位偶像的一次互动，她称这是她一生中“最色情的经历”</a> 。</p><p>这位女演员表示，当她在 20 世纪 80 年代中期一起拍摄电影《<i>绝对初学者》</i>时，她对这位歌手“完全敬畏”。</p><p> “我也被迷惑了，以为他会爱上我，然后我们就私奔。当然，当我在排队的时候，他只是握了我的手，然后就沿着队伍走，我被压垮了。”</p><p> “但有一天，我正在化妆，他把头探进门里打招呼。他走过来，拿起一把刷子，开始帮我梳理头发。他什么也没说，只是擦了擦，然后就走开了。这是我一生中最色情的经历。”</p><p> <i>《我在那儿：摇滚生活的快讯》</i>现已由西蒙与舒斯特出版。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/heres-how-david-bowie-used-to-disguise-himself-in-public-3763907">《大卫·鲍伊 (David Bowie) 在公共场合如何伪装自己》</a>一文首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ;
